sts":"","UR":"","OBC":"","SC":"","ST":"","EWS":""}],"salary_details":{"pay_scale":"Rs. 19900 - 215900 Per Month","salary":"Rs. 19900 - 215900 Per Month","details":""},"selection_process":["Written Exam","Document Verification"],"exam_pattern":[],"syllabus":[],"physical_eligibility":{"height":"","chest":"","running":"","weight":""},"how_to_apply":["Step 1: Download Application Proforma (Annexure-II) and eligibility conditions (Annexure-I) from www.nclt.gov.in under \"Career\".","Step 2: Fill in Annexure-II completely. Attach self-attested passport size coloured photograph. State clearly in Section 19 how you are best suited for the post.","Step 3: Attach all required documents (see list below).","Step 4: Submit the complete application to your Employer/Head of Office/Forwarding Authority for certification and forwarding.","Step 5: Forwarding authority sends the complete application to the Secretary, NCLT on or before the last date."],"important_instructions":["Applications must be submitted through proper channel only - via Employer/Head of Office/Forwarding Authority. Direct applications will not be accepted.","Candidates who apply will NOT be allowed to withdraw their application subsequently. Candidates unwilling to join upon selection must NOT apply.","Absorption into NCLT is NOT a matter of right. It will be done only based on NCLT's need and as per NCLT Recruitment Rules 2020. Absorption can be considered only after 1 year of satisfactory deputation.","Vacancy position is tentative and may increase or decrease. Selected candidates will serve only at the specific NCLT Bench for which they are selected.","GPRA benefit: Only officers already availing GPRA in their parent body can continue this benefit after joining NCLT on deputation. Others are not eligible to apply for GPRA on joining NCLT.","Cadre authorities must verify that all particulars sent by their officers are correct as per official records before forwarding applications.","Pre-01.01.2016 regular service will be treated as service in the corresponding level of the 7th CPC pay matrix for eligibility determination.","NCLT Recruitment Rules 2020 are available on www.nclt.gov.in under \"Career\" - candidates must read these before applying.","Applications not accompanied by all required documents, or received after the last date, will not be considered under any circumstances.","All corrigenda/updates will be published on www.nclt.gov.in - visit regularly."],"important_links":{"apply_online":"","official_website":"https://nclt.gov.in/","notification_pdf":"https://nclt.gov.in/sites/default/files/Career/Advt%20for%20Deputation%20for%20all%20posts%20dated%2021.05.2026.pdf","click_here":[{"text":"Download NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026 Official Notification","url":"https://nclt.gov.in/"},{"text":"Click here","url":"https://nclt.gov.in/sites/default/files/Career/Advt%20for%20Deputation%20for%20all%20posts%20dated%2021.05.2026.pdf"},{"text":"Click Here","url":"https://web.arattai.in/@freejobalertcom"}]},"faq":[{"question":"What is the last date to apply for NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026?","answer":"The last date to apply is 60 days from the date of publication in Employment News / Rozgar Samachar."},{"question":"How many vacancies are available in NCLT Recruitment 2026?","answer":"A total of 106 vacancies are available across multiple posts and NCLT benches in India."},{"question":"What is the mode of application for NCLT Deputation Vacancy 2026?","answer":"The application process is offline only and must be submitted through proper channel via the employer/forwarding authority."},{"question":"Who can apply for NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026?","answer":"Only serving Central/State Government officers, UT employees, or officials from courts/tribunals/statutory bodies are eligible."},{"question":"What is the maximum age limit for NCLT Deputation posts?","answer":"The maximum age limit is 56 years as on the closing date of application submission."},{"question":"Is there any application fee for NCLT Recruitment 2026?","answer":"There is no application fee required for this deputation-based recruitment."},{"question":"What is the selection process for NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026?","answer":"Selection is based on scrutiny of applications, APAR/ACR records, experience, and assessment by a Selection Committee."},{"question":"What is the salary for NCLT posts in 2026 recruitment?","answer":"Salary ranges from Level-2 (₹19,900) to Level-13 (₹2,15,900) as per the 7th CPC Pay Matrix."},{"question":"What is the duration of deputation in NCLT Recruitment 2026?","answer":"The deputation period is initially 3 years or until further orders, whichever is earlier."},{"question":"Can candidates get permanent absorption in NCLT after deputation?","answer":"Absorption may be considered after 1 year of deputation, but it is not guaranteed and depends on NCLT requirements."}],"seo_tags":["National Company Law Tribunal Staff Car Driver","UDC and More Recruitment 2026","NCLT Recruitment 2026","Latest NCLT Jobs","NCLT Staff Car Driver","UDC and More Jobs 2026","NCLT Staff Car Driver","UDC and More Careers"],"category":"10th Pass"},"basic_details":{"job_title":"NCLT Recruitment 2026 - Apply Offline for 106 Staff Car Driver, UDC and More Posts","last_updated":"2026-05-26T16:19:40+05:30","organization_name":"National Company Law Tribunal","post_name":"Joint Registrar, Deputy Registrar, Assistant Registrar, Programmer, Court Officer, Private Secretary, Senior Legal Assistant, Assistant, Stenographer Grade-I/Personal Assistant, Cashier, Record Assistant, Upper Division Clerk, Staff Car Driver","total_vacancies":"106 vacancies","notification_number":"21/05/2026","application_mode":"Offline only - through proper channel (via Employer/Head of Office/Forwarding Authority)","job_type":"Temporary","short_information":"The NCLT Recruitment 2026 notification has been released for a total of 106 Staff Car Driver, UDC and More vacancies. The Offline application pr