y that all particulars sent by their officers are correct as per official records before forwarding applications.","Pre-01.01.2016 regular service will be treated as service in the corresponding level of the 7th CPC pay matrix for eligibility determination.","NCLT Recruitment Rules 2020 are available on www.nclt.gov.in under \"Career\" - candidates must read these before applying.","Applications not accompanied by all required documents, or received after the last date, will not be considered under any circumstances.","All corrigenda/updates will be published on www.nclt.gov.in - visit regularly."],"important_links":{"apply_online":"","official_website":"https://nclt.gov.in/","notification_pdf":"https://nclt.gov.in/sites/default/files/Career/Advt%20for%20Deputation%20for%20all%20posts%20dated%2021.05.2026.pdf","click_here":[{"text":"Download NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026 Official Notification","url":"https://nclt.gov.in/"},{"text":"Click here","url":"https://nclt.gov.in/sites/default/files/Career/Advt%20for%20Deputation%20for%20all%20posts%20dated%2021.05.2026.pdf"},{"text":"Click Here","url":"https://web.arattai.in/@freejobalertcom"}]},"faq":[{"question":"What is the last date to apply for NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026?","answer":"The last date to apply is 60 days from the date of publication in Employment News / Rozgar Samachar."},{"question":"How many vacancies are available in NCLT Recruitment 2026?","answer":"A total of 106 vacancies are available across multiple posts and NCLT benches in India."},{"question":"What is the mode of application for NCLT Deputation Vacancy 2026?","answer":"The application process is offline only and must be submitted through proper channel via the employer/forwarding authority."},{"question":"Who can apply for NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026?","answer":"Only serving Central/State Government officers, UT employees, or officials from courts/tribunals/statutory bodies are eligible."},{"question":"What is the maximum age limit for NCLT Deputation posts?","answer":"The maximum age limit is 56 years as on the closing date of application submission."},{"question":"Is there any application fee for NCLT Recruitment 2026?","answer":"There is no application fee required for this deputation-based recruitment."},{"question":"What is the selection process for NCLT Deputation Recruitment 2026?","answer":"Selection is based on scrutiny of applications, APAR/ACR records, experience, and assessment by a Selection Committee."},{"question":"What is the salary for NCLT posts in 2026 recruitment?","answer":"Salary ranges from Level-2 (₹19,900) to Level-13 (₹2,15,900) as per the 7th CPC Pay Matrix."},{"question":"What is the duration of deputation in NCLT Recruitment 2026?","answer":"The deputation period is initially 3 years or until further orders, whichever is earlier."},{"question":"Can candidates get permanent absorption in NCLT after deputation?","answer":"Absorption may be considered after 1 year of deputation, but it is not guaranteed and depends on NCLT requirements."}],"seo_tags":["National Company Law Tribunal Staff Car Driver","UDC and More Recruitment 2026","NCLT Recruitment 2026","Latest NCLT Jobs","NCLT Staff Car Driver","UDC and More Jobs 2026","NCLT Staff Car Driver","UDC and More Careers"]}